text:
Paul Yun Ji-chung (in Korean 윤지충 바오로) is a Korean Christian layman, martyr and Catholic Blessed, born in 1759 in Jinsan, in the province of Jeolla in Korea, died beheaded on December 8, 1791 in Jeonju, in Jeolla. Recognized as a martyr by the Catholic Church, he was beatified in 2014 by Pope Francis. Blessed Paul Yun Ji-chung is celebrated locally on December 8.
